commit.message:
Merge pull request #14 from alanplotko/develop

Complete dashboard
Complete dashboard (resolves #12)
Add hypotheses and complete main components for dashboard
Add dashboard views and calculate stats

Merge pull request #13 from alanplotko/feature-survey

Prep for Heroku and set up checkup process
Fix typo in dropdown

Update summary layout and add explanations

- Resolves #8
- Resolves #11
Fix summary click tracking
Add support for outbound links in both question and summary layouts
Remove dummy content inserts in script
Fix linter issues and optimize profile updates
Change session ids and isolate profiles
Add new demographics fields and clean up views

Fix issue with resubmissions and submit button

- Resuming no longer allows the last question to be redone
- Fix resubmission process
- Fix submit button visibility
- Show errors from inline form and responses
Fix issue with submit button not showing unless on error
Add demographics form (resolves #7)

Separate general routes from checkup routes and add error page

- Isolate and unload checkup routes
- Add error page for unresolved routes (404)
- Make quotation marks and naming consistent in index and error views
Isolate readily available content into separate folder

Restyle question layout and apply name changes

- Change colors for yes and no to remove bias (resolves #10)
- Rename survey system to follow suit with the online checkup (resolves #9)
Default port if not given
Update start script to use node
Set up Heroku node/npm versions
Get port from Heroku if on Heroku
Merge branch 'feature-survey' of github.com:alanplotko/Protect-Yourself into feature-survey

Add buzzwords for variety

- Add buzzwords array to allow for nicer name generation in testing
- Track results by how many are successfully added to the collection
- Update test generation to account for new fields in track model

Add new track listing view; change track model

- Rename route from survey.js to tracks.js; better representation of what it is
- Separate name and slug in track model (update views accordingly)
- Create new listing view for tracks
Add generic banner for test use

Clean up templates

- Make data passed to views consistent in structure
- Refactor how the button panel gets built up in the survey view

Complete survey functionality

- Allow for resuming survey from where last left off
- Allow for resubmitting survey if submission fails

Remove instances of passing path in routes and remove single line string

- Path now accessed via locals; no need to pass path everywhere
- Single line string replaced with strip-newlines package
